- When Supabase is configured: use Edge Functions for LLM and server-only logic; never expose API keys in the client

=== TASK ===
# Forecasting & Reports

## Overview
Develop the Forecasting & Reports page for LifeOps, enabling users to forecast future cash flow, run scenario projections, and export month-end reports. This page must integrate with the Finance Automation suite (transaction ingestion, categorization, subscriptions, anomaly detection, forecasting, and monthly close workflows) and provide an intuitive, enterprise-grade UI that supports fast forecasting cycles, scenario planning, and auditable report exports. The implementation must be robust against null/undefined values and guard all array operations per the project’s runtime safety standards.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A comprehensive Forecasting & Reports hub that visualizes rolling cashflow forecasts, supports scenario-based projections, and exports month-end accounting reports (PDF/CSV). It also surfaces agent-driven insights and recommendations to optimize spend and manage deferred revenue.

Goals:
- Allow users to generate and compare forecast scenarios (baseline, upside, downside, custom inputs).
- Enable scenario builder to adjust income, expenses, subscriptions, and anomalies inputs; immediately reflect changes in charts and summary KPIs.
- Provide exportable month-end reports (PDF/CSV) with a clear audit trail, data provenance, and run artifacts.
- Surface agent insights and suggestions to reduce spend or optimize cash flow timing.
- Seamlessly integrate with Finance Automation workflows (ingestion, categorization, anomalies, forecasting, and monthly close).
- Ensure data integrity, permissions, and full traceability with reversible actions and run artifacts.

Connected features and data flows:
- Transaction ingestion, categorization, and subscription data feed forecasting inputs.
- Anomaly detection results feeding into forecast confidence and scenario adjustments.
- Monthly close workflow driving final reporting artifacts and approvals.
- Centralized audit trail for all forecast runs, scenario builds, exports, and inter-agent messages.

UI guidance and layout:
- Forecast graphs showing rolling forecast and scenario overlays with toggles (baseline, scenario A/B, confidence intervals).
- Scenario Builder panel with tunable assumptions (revenue, costs, seasonality, churn, renewal rates, subscription growth, one-off items).
- Report Exports panel for PDF/CSV generation with month-end metadata (period, account mappings, currency, permissions).
- Agent Insights panel delivering actionable recommendations.
- Left navigation and top breadcrumbs consistent with the LifeOps design system.

API integrations:
- No external APIs specified; all data originates from the LifeOps internal data layer (Finance Automation, Cronjobs, and Run Artifacts).
- Ensure API endpoints (internal) support data fetches for forecasts, scenarios, reports, and run histories with proper validation and security.

Accessibility and UX:
- Keyboard navigable controls, screen-reader friendly labels, and contrast-appropriate UI.
- Responsive layout that preserves data density for power users while maintaining clarity on smaller screens.

---

